article.headline: Toledo 63, Ball St. 55
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Toledo hit 12 of 17 3-point attempts, including four by Curtis Dennis, in a 63-55 victory over Ball State on Wednesday night. Dennis scored 17 points to lead the way for Toledo (12-14, 4-8 Mid-American West). Dominique Buckley scored 11 points and Julius Brown scored 10. Brown had five assists and Buckley had three steals. Ball State (12-12, 4-8) put up 30 shots from long range, but made just nine. Jesse Barry scored 17 for Ball State, Tyler Koch 13 and Jarrod Jones 11 to go with 15 rebounds. Ball State had a 46-30 advantage on the glass. Toledo had a 22-21 lead at halftime, and pulled away with a 41-34 second-half run.
